extends layout/layout.pug
block content

    div.section.container
        div.row
            div.col.s12.m10.offset-m1
                div.row

                    div.col.s12.m4
                        div.center.promo
                            i(class="material-icons") flash_on
                            p(class="promo-caption") Speeds up development
                            p(class="light center") We did most of the heavy lifting for you to provide a default stylings that incorporate our custom components. Additionally, we refined animations and transitions to provide a smoother experience for developers


                    div.col.s12.m4
                        div.center.promo
                            i(class="material-icons") group 
                            p(class="promo-caption") Speeds up development
                            p(class="light center") We did most of the heavy lifting for you to provide a default stylings that incorporate our custom components. Additionally, we refined animations and transitions to provide a smoother experience for developers


                    div.col.s12.m4
                        div.center.promo
                            i(class="material-icons") settings 
                            p(class="promo-caption") Speeds up development
                            p(class="light center") We did most of the heavy lifting for you to provide a default stylings that incorporate our custom components. Additionally, we refined animations and transitions to provide a smoother experience for developers
                
                hr

                form.col.s12
                    div.row
                        div.input-field.col.s12
                            input(id="word_entry" onkeyup="search_word()" type="text" class="validate")
                            label(for="word_entry") Enter The Word

                ul.collection.with-header#table
                    div.collection-header 
                        h4.header_word WORD
                        h4.header_meaning MEANING
                        
                    
                    each meaning, word in meaning_data 
                        ul.collection-item 
                            li.collection_word #{word}
                            .collection_splitter = 
                            li.collection_meaning #{meaning} 

                    



